### BADBIR Patient API - Test Endpoints
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7280

### 1. Register a new PATIENT (custom endpoint with identity verification)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "hsn953@gmail.com",
  "password": "Abcd1123!",
  "dateOfBirth": "1985-01-25",
  "initials": "HA",
  "nhsNumber": "0102030467",
  "chiNumber": null
}

### 2. Login with registered patient
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "hsn953@gmail.com",
  "password": "Abcd1123!"
}

### 3. Get user info (requires authentication - replace YOUR_TOKEN_HERE with token from login)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/identity/manage/info
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### ========================================
### Built-in Identity Endpoints (simple email/password only)
### ========================================

### 4. Register with built-in Identity endpoint (no patient verification)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/identity/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "simple@example.com",
  "password": "Test123!@#"
}

### 5. Login with built-in Identity endpoint
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/identity/login?useCookies=false
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "simple@example.com",
  "password": "Test123!@#"
}
